  <discussion>Paludella squarrosa is one of the most spectacular moss species in the flora area. The squarrose-recurved leaves (more squarrose than in any other species, including Rhytidiadelphus squarrosus), combined with the calcareous wet fen habitat are all that is needed for identification.</discussion>
